Budimex, Bank Millennium, NWR: Central European Equity Preview

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i   a n d   D o r o t a   B a r t y z e l
-- 
2011-04-27T06:34:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/budimex-bank-millennium-central-european-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in central
European markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company
names. Share prices are from the last close.  Poland ’s WIG20 Index rose 0.7 percent, the Czech PX Index
fell 0.3 percent and  Hungary ’s BUX Index rose 0.8 percent.  Budimex SA (BDX)  : Poland’s largest construction company
said net income fell to 46.7 million zloty ($17 million) from
53.3 million zloty a year earlier. That compares with the 35.5
million-zloty mean estimate of five analysts surveyed by
Bloomberg. Budimex gained 1.6 percent to 109.2 zloty.  Bank Millennium SA (MIL)  : The Polish unit of Banco
Comercial Portugues SA said first-quarter net income rose 49
percent to 101 million zloty. That missed the 112.7 million
zloty average estimate of six analysts surveyed by Bloomberg
News. Millennium rose 0.9 percent to 5.74 zloty.  New World Resources NV (NWR)  : The largest Czech coking
coal producer was cut to “hold” from “buy” at ING Groep NV.
Its shares declined 1.8 percent to 272 koruna.  To contact the reporters on this story:
